My take
Social media done right isnâ€™t hard or complicated. Yet control freakery combined with the overwhelming urge to fill a sales pipeline has left a stain on the incumbent networks that is hard to imagine getting cleaned up any time soon. But it is possible to nurture a highly knowledgeable community and still push messages to them.
Marriott has demonstrated that when you set something up and allow the community to come together in its own time and in its own way then good things happen that benefits everyone. The proofÂ is in the eating.Â That community now spans more than 160,000 people on one Twitter account alone recording close to 640,000 Tweets over a nine-year period. The European version has more than 20,000 people from a standing start in 2016.
Unfortunately, too many businesses have viewed these networks as a cheap way to do the same old marketing as they always did, forgetting the customer experience along the way.
